given n : int

letting I be domain int(1..n)
letting H be domain int(1..n/2)
letting IM be domain matrix indexed by [H, H] of H
letting M be domain matrix indexed by [I, I, H] of I
letting MH be domain matrix indexed by [I, H] of H
letting MN be domain matrix indexed by [I, I, H] of MH
letting R be domain record { a: M, b: record { b1: MN, b2: tuple(MH, MN) } }

$ no constraints. DDoS your machine with conjure solutions today! fun for the whole family :)
find x: R
